a986df20-0f18-49e7-96ad-043d05ac1ccc.label: Ulman's early aesthetic skills included making and selling clothes, a pursuit which provided the necessary funds to travel and network in bigger cities. This deep engagement with visual culture taught her how to meticulously stage photographs to manage the audience's perception of her social and class markers, concealing her limited resources.
